Hot, Property & Building, Teva: Israel Equity Preview

-- B y   S h a r o n   W r o b e l
-- 
2011-07-20T07:57:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-20/hot-property-building-and-teva-israeli-equity-preview.html
(Corrects definition of Natural Resource in fourth
paragraph.)  The following stocks may rise or
fall in Israeli markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after
the company names and prices are from the last close unless
otherwise stated.  The TA-25 Index gained 0.7 percent to 1,248.76 in  Tel Aviv .  Hot Telecommunication System Ltd. (HOT)  : The cable and
telecommunications company said its board approved the
acquisition of MIRS Communication Ltd., a wireless operator, for
1.3 billion shekels ($378 million). Hot rose less than 0.1
percent to 60.40 shekels.  Natural Resource Holdings Ltd. (NRH)  : An investor in
commodities and natural resource companies said it’s considering
dual-listing its shares in the U.S. Natural Resource increased
4.4 percent to 4.529 shekels.  Property & Building Corp. (PTBL)  : The real-estate
company plans to reassess the value of its investment-property
portfolio and based on that revaluation expects to report
second-quarter net income of 60 million shekels to 90 million
shekels. Property & Building advanced 1.4 percent to 230.50
shekels.  Teva Pharmaceutical Industries Ltd. (TEVA)  : The world’s
largest generic drugmaker expanded its licensing agreement with
Cel-Sci Corp. for the cancer drug Multikine to include Croatia
and Serbia. Teva lost 0.4 percent to 164 shekels.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Wrobel in Tel Aviv at 
